title: Expenses and benefits: gifts to employees

heading_context: Expenses and benefits: gifts to employees
chunks.html_content: As an employer providing gifts to your employees, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations.
chunks.plain_content:
Expenses and benefits: gifts to employees
As an employer providing gifts to your employees, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations.

heading_context: Expenses and benefits: gifts to employees
chunks.html_content: There are different rules depending on the type of gift you give. Follow the reporting and payment rules for the specific item.
chunks.plain_content:
Expenses and benefits: gifts to employees
Businesses
There are different rules depending on the type of gift you give. Follow the reporting and payment rules for the specific item.

heading_context: Expenses and benefits: gifts to employees
chunks.html_content: If you’re self-employed, you don’t have to report or pay tax or National Insurance on personal gifts (eg birthday or wedding presents) that you give to employees.
chunks.plain_content:
Expenses and benefits: gifts to employees
Self-employed
If you’re self-employed, you don’t have to report or pay tax or National Insurance on personal gifts (eg birthday or wedding presents) that you give to employees.
